text: Program: Beam to users w/500ma 5min. freq. fill mode. Beam lines: All open. Faults/Alarms: None this shift. Experiments: No concerns expressed. Rad samples @BL11-2

title: 11-2 has very bad amplitude instability, CATER Id: 155396(TEC)
text: \This early morning ACR called about MOD 11-2 has really bad phase jitter. They asked me to look for spare SSSB for replacement. Removed SSSB from 20-3C, modified and swapped it. Used power meter to measure output and set it at spec. Dave said it is good for now. Will check tomorrow... SSSB: IN-SN004, OUT- 18028092

title: 30-3 KHD fault. CATER Id: 155403(TEC)
text: ACR called about this station. Found the focus magnet trim ps bad. Replaced it but logfault showed the klystron filament in red. TS and found the fuse open. Replaced it and now both klys and thyratron are time out. After one hour, turn back on OK. Notified ACR.

title: A note about phasing LI11
text: After phasing a sector of klystrons, one common way of updating the gold in the SCP is to simply "Accept KLYS Gold" for the entire sector rather than updating each individually after the scan. However in LI11, due to the mishmash of SCP/EPICS controls on 11-1 and 11-2, if you accept KLYS gold on the entirety of LI11 it will screw things up and be a pain for the FACET people to dig out. This has happened at least once before (https://mccelog.slac.stanford.edu/elog/wbin/elog_item.php?elog_id=1124230) and almost happened again this morning.

title: 12-4 KPHR was stuck at the wraparound point (near +350 deg), forced it -360 degrees to ~0
text: Dumb thing I did to fix it: 12-4 KPHR was around +350 degrees. Phase scans of +/- 50 degrees from this point were not too useful based on the corrplot plotting, but it looked like the phase wanted to be around the +360/-360 point. Could not caput the KPHR by -360 degrees. Couldn't push the phase knob more than -190 degrees. Instead, I entered a PDES of -180, trimmed, re-golded, then entered a PDES again of -180, trimmed, and re-golded. The phase would not trim to 0 at this point (station showed "lost phase"), so I swung the phase knob around until it found a phase where it would trim, then walked it to 0 It seems like there must be a better way to do this

Suggestion for ~20 fs pulses now and the foil later
text: Just spoke with Alex in ACR. With TMO moving on from XLEAP, next request is 20-30 fs pulses. They'd like a max of 1.5 mJ (with the 4 undulators out still) even while at half the charge/duration. Strongly suggesting we reload the 6.3 GeV config from the first TMO shifts. This lets us go to higher K, so easier to keep up the flux. Plus later they may/will ask for the slotted foil for even shorter pulses. This should also be better and easier with BC2 at 4.5 GeV.

title: Suggestion for ~20 fs pulses now and the foil later
text: Just spoke with Alex in ACR. With TMO moving on from XLEAP, next request is 20-30 fs pulses. They'd like a max of 1.5 mJ (with the 4 undulators out still) even while at half the charge/duration. Strongly suggesting we reload the 6.3 GeV config from the first TMO shifts.
